@HargraveRev Thank you for your helpful reply. 

What is that idea doing up as #2 — or #1, as you say? This is an essential principle for living a good life, or building a good community? 

Because that's what I would expect the Ten Commandments to be, no?

@HargraveRev I agree. 

But it's just a first pass by a fledgling machine intelligence. Up for improvement. 

And I've never understood "no graven images," tbh. How did that make anyone's list?

@AmoneyResists @HC_Richardson Somehow, the Sedition Caucus is now negotiating for more power. 

One of the consequences of no consequences for insurrection. 

Sad!

@ntnsndr Yup. 

And my hope fades when every other decision Musk makes seems like intentional sabotage aimed to crater Twitter. 

Sigh.

@debs, thank you!

@pforti, I love your post. Somehow, relationships and trust became taboo, "soft" skills, not necessary in the hard business world. 

But if Elon understood just a smidge of this...

@DrMatthewSweet @Alheri @nationaltrust Thank you. 

I love Turner's The Fighting Temeraire, as a depiction of technological change. 

Had no idea of the Zong massacre, or Turner's Slave Ship painting: https://t.co/PyPpwX4WXb

@BillSeitz Haven't thought it through, but if they can prove they're the same person posting as a pseud, that should work. 

Or pseudonymity is a paid feature...

Your recommendation?

@nils_gilman So... aren't ideological litmus tests common for social movements? 

Far as I can tell, the planet's most influential religion requires pledging that its hero was born from a virgin, performed miracles, died and was resurrected. 

Swap in QAnon and you have trouble.

@DropboxSupport Thanks for your help. What got me extra irritated was I tried the help system, which got me to a blank page, not the one you just shared. 

Also: I was trying to delete in the left-hand nav menu and had to pop a level up b4 seeing the three dots. 

Now deleted. Tx.

@Dropbox your UX for casual users is atrocious. 

From the browser UI, can't find a way to delete a folder, which I created accidentally because I'm not connected to someone else's shared folder correctly. 

Srsly? How are you so popular?

@PardonMusings @MikeHudema Agree that facts don't usually work. https://t.co/ArRk4MLlNo

So... drama? Friends' harrowing stories? Relatives suffering? 

Or just firsthand catastrophe?

Love this! There's no single answer, but rather a strong need for coordination. 

